{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":507,"text":"Today I want to talk to you\nabout the mathematics of love."},{"time":5200,"text":"Now, I think that we can all agree"},{"time":6853,"text":"that mathematicians\nare famously excellent at finding love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10479,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11906,"text":"But it's not just because\nof our dashing personalities,"},{"time":14897,"text":"superior conversational skills\nand excellent pencil cases."},{"time":20083,"text":"It's also because we've actually done\nan awful lot of work into the maths"},{"time":23850,"text":"of how to find the perfect partner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26350,"text":"Now, in my favorite paper\non the subject, which is entitled,"},{"time":30053,"text":"\"Why I Don't Have a Girlfriend\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":31940,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":33371,"text":"Peter Backus tries to rate\nhis chances of finding love."},{"time":37013,"text":"Now, Peter's not a very greedy man."},{"time":39266,"text":"Of all of the available women in the UK,"},{"time":41542,"text":"all Peter's looking for\nis somebody who lives near him,"},{"time":45061,"text":"somebody in the right age range,"},{"time":46891,"text":"somebody with a university degree,"},{"time":49837,"text":"somebody he's likely to get on well with,"},{"time":51843,"text":"somebody who's likely to be attractive,"},{"time":53810,"text":"somebody who's likely\nto find him attractive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56140,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":59218,"text":"And comes up with an estimate\nof 26 women in the whole of the UK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64032,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":65235,"text":"It's not looking very good, is it Peter?"},{"time":67292,"text":"Now, just to put that into perspective,"},{"time":69270,"text":"that's about 400 times fewer\nthan the best estimates"},{"time":72574,"text":"of how many intelligent\nextraterrestrial life forms there are."},{"time":76299,"text":"And it also gives Peter\na 1 in 285,000 chance"},{"time":81617,"text":"of bumping into any one\nof these special ladies"},{"time":83902,"text":"on a given night out."},{"time":85465,"text":"I'd like to think\nthat's why mathematicians"},{"time":87491,"text":"don't really bother\ngoing on nights out anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91109,"text":"The thing is that I personally\ndon't subscribe"},{"time":93389,"text":"to such a pessimistic view."},{"time":95069,"text":"Because I know,\njust as well as all of you do,"},{"time":97682,"text":"that love doesn't really work like that."},{"time":100078,"text":"Human emotion isn't neatly ordered\nand rational and easily predictable."},{"time":105396,"text":"But I also know that that doesn't mean"},{"time":107641,"text":"that mathematics hasn't got something\nthat it can offer us,"},{"time":110945,"text":"because, love, as with most of life,\nis full of patterns"},{"time":114715,"text":"and mathematics is, ultimately,\nall about the study of patterns."},{"time":119165,"text":"Patterns from predicting the weather\nto the fluctuations in the stock market,"},{"time":123533,"text":"to the movement of the planets\nor the growth of cities."},{"time":126588,"text":"And if we're being honest,\nnone of those things"},{"time":128902,"text":"are exactly neatly ordered\nand easily predictable, either."},{"time":132966,"text":"Because I believe that mathematics\nis so powerful that it has the potential"},{"time":138168,"text":"to offer us a new way of looking\nat almost anything."},{"time":141513,"text":"Even something as mysterious as love."},{"time":144979,"text":"And so, to try to persuade you"},{"time":146675,"text":"of how totally amazing, excellent\nand relevant mathematics is,"},{"time":151392,"text":"I want to give you my top three\nmathematically verifiable tips for love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158651,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":160440,"text":"OK, so Top Tip #1:"},{"time":162104,"text":"How to win at online dating."},{"time":166567,"text":"So my favorite online dating\nwebsite is OkCupid,"},{"time":169962,"text":"not least because it was started\nby a group of mathematicians."},{"time":173574,"text":"Now, because they're mathematicians,"},{"time":175343,"text":"they have been collecting data"},{"time":176844,"text":"on everybody who uses their site\nfor almost a decade."},{"time":180364,"text":"And they've been trying\nto search for patterns"},{"time":182538,"text":"in the way that we talk about ourselves"},{"time":184425,"text":"and the way that we interact\nwith each other"},{"time":186508,"text":"on an online dating website."},{"time":187876,"text":"And they've come up with some\nseriously interesting findings."},{"time":190825,"text":"But my particular favorite"},{"time":192447,"text":"is that it turns out\nthat on an online dating website,"},{"time":195827,"text":"how attractive you are\ndoes not dictate how popular you are,"},{"time":201511,"text":"and actually, having people\nthink that you're ugly"},{"time":205391,"text":"can work to your advantage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207469,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":208643,"text":"Let me show you how this works."},{"time":210337,"text":"In a thankfully voluntary\nsection of OkCupid,"},{"time":214740,"text":"you are allowed to rate\nhow attractive you think people are"},{"time":217565,"text":"on a scale between one and five."},{"time":219874,"text":"Now, if we compare this score,\nthe average score,"},{"time":222879,"text":"to how many messages\na selection of people receive,"},{"time":226044,"text":"you can begin to get a sense"},{"time":227591,"text":"of how attractiveness links to popularity\non an online dating website."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232023,"text":"This is the graph the OkCupid guys\nhave come up with."},{"time":235389,"text":"And the important thing to notice\nis that it's not totally true"},{"time":238407,"text":"that the more attractive you are,\nthe more messages you get."},{"time":241256,"text":"But the question arises then\nof what is it about people up here"},{"time":245535,"text":"who are so much more popular\nthan people down here,"},{"time":249422,"text":"even though they have the same\nscore of attractiveness?"},{"time":252542,"text":"And the reason why is that it's not just\nstraightforward looks that are important."},{"time":256699,"text":"So let me try to illustrate\ntheir findings with an example."},{"time":259530,"text":"So if you take someone like\nPortia de Rossi, for example,"},{"time":263472,"text":"everybody agrees that Portia de Rossi\nis a very beautiful woman."},{"time":267976,"text":"Nobody thinks that she's ugly,\nbut she's not a supermodel, either."},{"time":271718,"text":"If you compare Portia de Rossi\nto someone like Sarah Jessica Parker,"},{"time":276333,"text":"now, a lot of people,\nmyself included, I should say,"},{"time":280039,"text":"think that Sarah Jessica Parker\nis seriously fabulous"},{"time":284320,"text":"and possibly one\nof the most beautiful creatures"},{"time":286990,"text":"to have ever have walked\non the face of the Earth."},{"time":289404,"text":"But some other people,\ni.e., most of the Internet ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294193,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296287,"text":"seem to think that she looks\na bit like a horse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298697,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":301510,"text":"Now, I think that if you ask people\nhow attractive they thought"},{"time":305627,"text":"Jessica Parker or Portia de Rossi were,"},{"time":307559,"text":"and you ask them to give\nthem a score between one and five"},{"time":310491,"text":"I reckon that they'd average out\nto have roughly the same score."},{"time":313535,"text":"But the way that people would vote\nwould be very different."},{"time":316323,"text":"So Portia's scores would\nall be clustered around the four"},{"time":319049,"text":"because everybody agrees\nthat she's very beautiful,"},{"time":321504,"text":"whereas Sarah Jessica Parker\ncompletely divides opinion."},{"time":324242,"text":"There'd be a huge spread in her scores."},{"time":326242,"text":"And actually it's this spread that counts."},{"time":328615,"text":"It's this spread\nthat makes you more popular"},{"time":330865,"text":"on an online Internet dating website."},{"time":333065,"text":"So what that means then"},{"time":334277,"text":"is that if some people\nthink that you're attractive,"},{"time":336906,"text":"you're actually better off"},{"time":338791,"text":"having some other people\nthink that you're a massive minger."},{"time":343935,"text":"That's much better\nthan everybody just thinking"},{"time":346173,"text":"that you're the cute girl next door."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348260,"text":"Now, I think this begins\nto make a bit more sense"},{"time":350609,"text":"when you think in terms of the people\nwho are sending these messages."},{"time":353903,"text":"So let's say that you think\nsomebody's attractive,"},{"time":356285,"text":"but you suspect that other people\nwon't necessarily be that interested."},{"time":360274,"text":"That means there's\nless competition for you"},{"time":362543,"text":"and it's an extra incentive\nfor you to get in touch."},{"time":365349,"text":"Whereas compare that\nto if you think somebody is attractive"},{"time":368158,"text":"but you suspect that everybody\nis going to think they're attractive."},{"time":371399,"text":"Well, why would you bother\nhumiliating yourself, let's be honest?"},{"time":375077,"text":"But here's where the really\ninteresting part comes."},{"time":377494,"text":"Because when people choose the pictures\nthat they use on an online dating website,"},{"time":381698,"text":"they often try to minimize the things"},{"time":383898,"text":"that they think some people\nwill find unattractive."},{"time":387160,"text":"The classic example is people\nwho are, perhaps, a little bit overweight"},{"time":391215,"text":"deliberately choosing\na very cropped photo,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":393681,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":395056,"text":"or bald men, for example,"},{"time":396840,"text":"deliberately choosing pictures\nwhere they're wearing hats."},{"time":399812,"text":"But actually this is the opposite\nof what you should do"},{"time":402426,"text":"if you want to be successful."},{"time":403840,"text":"You should really, instead,"},{"time":405198,"text":"play up to whatever it is\nthat makes you different,"},{"time":408380,"text":"even if you think that some people\nwill find it unattractive."},{"time":412555,"text":"Because the people who fancy you\nare just going to fancy you anyway,"},{"time":415790,"text":"and the unimportant losers who don't,\nwell, they only play up to your advantage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420370,"text":"OK, Top Tip #2:\nHow to pick the perfect partner."},{"time":422947,"text":"So let's imagine then\nthat you're a roaring success"},{"time":425624,"text":"on the dating scene."},{"time":427189,"text":"But the question arises\nof how do you then convert that success"},{"time":431748,"text":"into longer-term happiness,"},{"time":434323,"text":"and in particular, how do you decide\nwhen is the right time to settle down?"},{"time":439437,"text":"Now generally,\nit's not advisable to just cash in"},{"time":442269,"text":"and marry the first person who comes along\nand shows you any interest at all."},{"time":446416,"text":"But, equally, you don't really\nwant to leave it too long"},{"time":449561,"text":"if you want to maximize your chance\nof long-term happiness."},{"time":452355,"text":"As my favorite author,\nJane Austen, puts it,"},{"time":455843,"text":"\"An unmarried woman of seven and twenty"},{"time":458061,"text":"can never hope to feel\nor inspire affection again.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":461517,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":464206,"text":"Thanks a lot, Jane."},{"time":465412,"text":"What do you know about love?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":466849,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":467956,"text":"So the question is then,"},{"time":469889,"text":"how do you know when\nis the right time to settle down,"},{"time":472502,"text":"given all the people\nthat you can date in your lifetime?"},{"time":475154,"text":"Thankfully, there's a rather delicious bit\nof mathematics that we can use"},{"time":478628,"text":"to help us out here,\ncalled optimal stopping theory."},{"time":481196,"text":"So let's imagine, then,"},{"time":483201,"text":"that you start dating when you're 15"},{"time":485827,"text":"and ideally, you'd like to be married\nby the time that you're 35."},{"time":489620,"text":"And there's a number of people"},{"time":491086,"text":"that you could potentially\ndate across your lifetime,"},{"time":493607,"text":"and they'll be at varying\nlevels of goodness."},{"time":495759,"text":"Now the rules are that once\nyou cash in and get married,"},{"time":498448,"text":"you can't look ahead to see\nwhat you could have had,"},{"time":500902,"text":"and equally, you can't go back\nand change your mind."},{"time":503459,"text":"In my experience at least,"},{"time":505082,"text":"I find that typically people\ndon't much like being recalled"},{"time":507904,"text":"years after being passed up\nfor somebody else, or that's just me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513146,"text":"So the math says then\nthat what you should do"},{"time":516363,"text":"in the first 37 percent\nof your dating window,"},{"time":519558,"text":"you should just reject everybody\nas serious marriage potential."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523339,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":525513,"text":"And then, you should pick\nthe next person that comes along"},{"time":529161,"text":"that is better than everybody\nthat you've seen before."},{"time":532154,"text":"So here's the example."},{"time":533599,"text":"Now if you do this, it can be\nmathematically proven, in fact,"},{"time":536490,"text":"that this is the best possible way"},{"time":538975,"text":"of maximizing your chances\nof finding the perfect partner."},{"time":543328,"text":"Now unfortunately, I have to tell you that\nthis method does come with some risks."},{"time":548604,"text":"For instance, imagine\nif your perfect partner appeared"},{"time":553437,"text":"during your first 37 percent."},{"time":556143,"text":"Now, unfortunately,\nyou'd have to reject them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558939,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":562129,"text":"Now, if you're following the maths,"},{"time":564268,"text":"I'm afraid no one else comes along"},{"time":565925,"text":"that's better than anyone\nyou've seen before,"},{"time":568220,"text":"so you have to go on\nrejecting everyone and die alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572093,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":574560,"text":"Probably surrounded by cats ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576100,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":577838,"text":"nibbling at your remains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579429,"text":"OK, another risk is,\nlet's imagine, instead,"},{"time":583422,"text":"that the first people that you dated\nin your first 37 percent"},{"time":586562,"text":"are just incredibly dull,\nboring, terrible people."},{"time":590839,"text":"That's OK, because\nyou're in your rejection phase,"},{"time":593245,"text":"so that's fine, you can reject them."},{"time":594984,"text":"But then imagine\nthe next person to come along"},{"time":598381,"text":"is just marginally less boring,\ndull and terrible ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601735,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":602858,"text":"than everybody that you've seen before."},{"time":604780,"text":"Now, if you are following the maths,\nI'm afraid you have to marry them ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608399,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":609478,"text":"and end up in a relationship\nwhich is, frankly, suboptimal."},{"time":612645,"text":"Sorry about that."},{"time":613822,"text":"But I do think that there's an opportunity\nhere for Hallmark to cash in on"},{"time":617346,"text":"and really cater for this market."},{"time":618952,"text":"A Valentine's Day card like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620559,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":621739,"text":"\"My darling husband,\nyou are marginally less terrible"},{"time":624765,"text":"than the first 37 percent\nof people I dated.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":626943,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":628597,"text":"It's actually more romantic\nthan I normally manage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631745,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":633240,"text":"OK, so this method doesn't give you\na 100 percent success rate,"},{"time":637925,"text":"but there's no other possible\nstrategy that can do any better."},{"time":641384,"text":"And actually, in the wild,\nthere are certain types of fish"},{"time":644838,"text":"which follow and employ\nthis exact strategy."},{"time":647679,"text":"So they reject every possible\nsuitor that turns up"},{"time":650456,"text":"in the first 37 percent\nof the mating season,"},{"time":653169,"text":"and then they pick the next fish\nthat comes along after that window"},{"time":656944,"text":"that's, I don't know, bigger and burlier"},{"time":659123,"text":"than all of the fish\nthat they've seen before."},{"time":661725,"text":"I also think that subconsciously,\nhumans, we do sort of do this anyway."},{"time":666626,"text":"We give ourselves a little bit of time\nto play the field,"},{"time":669495,"text":"get a feel for the marketplace\nor whatever when we're young."},{"time":673115,"text":"And then we only start looking seriously\nat potential marriage candidates"},{"time":677729,"text":"once we hit our mid-to-late 20s."},{"time":679780,"text":"I think this is conclusive proof,\nif ever it were needed,"},{"time":683014,"text":"that everybody's brains are prewired\nto be just a little bit mathematical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687450,"text":"OK, so that was Top Tip #2."},{"time":689477,"text":"Now, Top Tip #3: How to avoid divorce."},{"time":693351,"text":"OK, so let's imagine then\nthat you picked your perfect partner"},{"time":696299,"text":"and you're settling into\na lifelong relationship with them."},{"time":700552,"text":"Now, I like to think that everybody\nwould ideally like to avoid divorce,"},{"time":704562,"text":"apart from, I don't know,\nPiers Morgan's wife, maybe?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":708832,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":710185,"text":"But it's a sad fact of modern life"},{"time":712629,"text":"that one in two marriages\nin the States ends in divorce,"},{"time":715913,"text":"with the rest of the world\nnot being far behind."},{"time":719729,"text":"Now, you can be forgiven, perhaps"},{"time":721587,"text":"for thinking that the arguments\nthat precede a marital breakup"},{"time":725344,"text":"are not an ideal candidate\nfor mathematical investigation."},{"time":729359,"text":"For one thing, it's very hard to know"},{"time":731165,"text":"what you should be measuring\nor what you should be quantifying."},{"time":734266,"text":"But this didn't stop a psychologist,\nJohn Gottman, who did exactly that."},{"time":740473,"text":"Gottman observed hundreds of couples\nhaving a conversation"},{"time":745734,"text":"and recorded, well,\neverything you can think of."},{"time":748064,"text":"So he recorded what was said\nin the conversation,"},{"time":750455,"text":"he recorded their skin conductivity,"},{"time":752772,"text":"he recorded their facial expressions,"},{"time":754859,"text":"their heart rates, their blood pressure,"},{"time":756874,"text":"basically everything apart from whether\nor not the wife was actually always right,"},{"time":763134,"text":"which incidentally she totally is."},{"time":766349,"text":"But what Gottman and his team found"},{"time":769022,"text":"was that one of the most\nimportant predictors"},{"time":772061,"text":"for whether or not a couple\nis going to get divorced"},{"time":774567,"text":"was how positive or negative each partner\nwas being in the conversation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779214,"text":"Now, couples that were very low-risk"},{"time":781568,"text":"scored a lot more positive points\non Gottman's scale than negative."},{"time":785861,"text":"Whereas bad relationships,"},{"time":788426,"text":"by which I mean,\nprobably going to get divorced,"},{"time":791197,"text":"they found themselves getting\ninto a spiral of negativity."},{"time":795578,"text":"Now just by using these very simple ideas,"},{"time":797862,"text":"Gottman and his group were able to predict"},{"time":800357,"text":"whether a given couple\nwas going to get divorced"},{"time":803103,"text":"with a 90 percent accuracy."},{"time":806005,"text":"But it wasn't until he teamed up\nwith a mathematician, James Murray,"},{"time":809318,"text":"that they really started to understand"},{"time":811233,"text":"what causes these negativity spirals\nand how they occur."},{"time":815751,"text":"And the results that they found,"},{"time":817308,"text":"I think, are just incredibly\nimpressively simple and interesting."},{"time":821981,"text":"So these equations predict how the wife\nor husband is going to respond"},{"time":826568,"text":"in their next turn of the conversation,"},{"time":828480,"text":"how positive or negative\nthey're going to be."},{"time":830637,"text":"And these equations depend on"},{"time":832046,"text":"the mood of the person\nwhen they're on their own,"},{"time":834376,"text":"the mood of the person when\nthey're with their partner,"},{"time":837014,"text":"but most importantly, they depend on"},{"time":838763,"text":"how much the husband and wife\ninfluence one another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842115,"text":"Now, I think it's important\nto point out at this stage,"},{"time":844746,"text":"that these exact equations\nhave also been shown"},{"time":848279,"text":"to be perfectly able at describing"},{"time":850498,"text":"what happens between two countries\nin an arms race."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855010,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":858300,"text":"So that an arguing couple\nspiraling into negativity"},{"time":861905,"text":"and teetering on the brink of divorce"},{"time":863834,"text":"is actually mathematically equivalent\nto the beginning of a nuclear war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":868107,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":871021,"text":"But the really important term\nin this equation"},{"time":873358,"text":"is the influence that people\nhave on one another,"},{"time":875877,"text":"and in particular, something called\n\"the negativity threshold.\""},{"time":879158,"text":"Now, the negativity threshold,"},{"time":880914,"text":"you can think of as\nhow annoying the husband can be"},{"time":885565,"text":"before the wife starts to get\nreally pissed off, and vice versa."},{"time":889852,"text":"Now, I always thought that good marriages\nwere about compromise and understanding"},{"time":894408,"text":"and allowing the person\nto have the space to be themselves."},{"time":897194,"text":"So I would have thought that perhaps\nthe most successful relationships"},{"time":900571,"text":"were ones where there was\na really high negativity threshold."},{"time":903875,"text":"Where couples let things go"},{"time":905692,"text":"and only brought things up\nif they really were a big deal."},{"time":908487,"text":"But actually, the mathematics\nand subsequent findings by the team"},{"time":912762,"text":"have shown the exact opposite is true."},{"time":915799,"text":"The best couples,\nor the most successful couples,"},{"time":918132,"text":"are the ones with a really low\nnegativity threshold."},{"time":921519,"text":"These are the couples\nthat don't let anything go unnoticed"},{"time":925177,"text":"and allow each other\nsome room to complain."},{"time":928399,"text":"These are the couples that are continually\ntrying to repair their own relationship,"},{"time":933657,"text":"that have a much more positive\noutlook on their marriage."},{"time":936424,"text":"Couples that don't let things go"},{"time":938516,"text":"and couples that don't let trivial things\nend up being a really big deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944426,"text":"Now of course, it takes a bit more\nthan just a low negativity threshold"},{"time":949708,"text":"and not compromising\nto have a successful relationship."},{"time":954100,"text":"But I think that it's quite interesting"},{"time":956650,"text":"to know that there is really\nmathematical evidence"},{"time":959028,"text":"to say that you should never\nlet the sun go down on your anger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":962480,"text":"So those are my top three tips"},{"time":964188,"text":"of how maths can help you\nwith love and relationships."},{"time":967383,"text":"But I hope, that aside from\ntheir use as tips,"},{"time":969802,"text":"they also give you a little bit of insight\ninto the power of mathematics."},{"time":973928,"text":"Because for me, equations\nand symbols aren't just a thing."},{"time":978684,"text":"They're a voice that speaks out\nabout the incredible richness of nature"},{"time":983119,"text":"and the startling simplicity"},{"time":984929,"text":"in the patterns that twist and turn\nand warp and evolve all around us,"},{"time":989766,"text":"from how the world works to how we behave."},{"time":992370,"text":"So I hope that perhaps,\nfor just a couple of you,"},{"time":994704,"text":"a little bit of insight\ninto the mathematics of love"},{"time":997213,"text":"can persuade you to have\na little bit more love for mathematics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1000534,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1001757,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}